[[Kernow|Kernowes]] yn drolla o '''Betty Stogs'''. Hi a drigas war woon ogas dhe [[:en:Towednack|Tewydnek]], [[Kernow]]. Yth esa mab hwegh mis dhedhi, mes diek ha omvodhek o hi. An [[:en:Fairy|fayys]] a withas an baban dispresyes, ena y dhehweles glan ha gorwedh war weli kewni.<ref>{{citation |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wA1glmqw9dYC&pg=PA95 |pages=95–100 |title=Popular romances of the west of England |volume=1 |author=Robert Hunt |chapter=Betty Stogs and Jan the Mounster}}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=The Folklore of Cornwall |page=93 |first1=Tony |last1=Deane |first2=Tony |last2=Shaw |year=1975 |publisher=Batsford}}</ref> Hengovek a'n ranndir ma yw an hwedhel; gwarnyans dhe vammow yw rag gwitha aga fleghes yn ewn, rag own an dus munys dh'aga hemeres.<ref>{{citation |pages=79–80 |title=Folklore and the Fantastic in Nineteenth-Century British Fiction |first=Jason Marc |last=Harristitle |publisher=Routledge |year=2016 |isbn=9781317134657}}</ref>

Hanow an korev ''Betty Stogs'' a dheu dhyworth venyn fugiethel. Y grefter yw 4% alcohol. Bregys yw yn [[:en:Skinner's Brewery|Bragji Skinner]] yn [[Truru]]. Ev a waynyas an pewas [[:En:CAMRA|CAMRA]] rag ''An Gwella Korev Hwerow'' yn 2008.<ref>{{citation |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SHh-4M_QxEsC&pg=PA85 |title=World's Best Beers |author=Ben McFarland |page=85}}</ref> Yma kan Sowsnek a-dro dhe'n korev ma.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.exmouthshantymen.com/songbook.php?id=149 |title=The original buoy band |publisher=Exmouth Shanty Men |date= |accessdate=2021-11-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dj7syT8s6B4 |title=Exmouth Shantymen - A Pint of Betty Stoggs |publisher=YouTube |date=2011-04-03 |accessdate=2021-11-09}}</ref>

